ting McIntyre's restrained approach to Charter jurisprudence, especially its relation to governmental legislation, with his upbringing in Moose Jaw during the Depression and his early career at the Bar. This is an original contribution to our understanding both of an important judge and an important era in Canadian legal history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357410640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773574106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773574106/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles